\b0 The client tier consists of a client program that makes requests to the middle tier. The middle tier is divided into a web tier and a business tier, which handle client requests and process application data, storing it in a permanent data store in the data tier.\par
Typically, multitiered applications have a client tier, a middle tier, and a data tier (often called the enterprise information systems tier). The client tier consists of a client program that makes requests to the middle tier. The middle tier is divided into a web tier and a business tier, which handle client requests and process application data, storing it in a permanent data store in the data tier.\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li360\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ul\b The Client Tier\ulnone\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Clients can be a web browser, a standalone application and other servers.\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li360\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ul\b The Middle Tier \ulnone\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The Web Tier \par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1080\sl276\slmult1\b0 The web tier consists of components that handle the interaction between clients and the business tier. Its primary tasks are the following:\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1440\sl276\slmult1 Dynamically generate content in various formats for the client\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Collect input from users of the client interface and return appropriate results from the components in the business tier\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Control the flow of screens or pages on the client\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Maintain the state of data for a user\rquote s session\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Perform some basic logic and hold some data temporarily in managed beans\b\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1080\sl276\slmult1\b0 Above we list some of the main Java EE technologies that are used in the web tier in Java EE applications:\b\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1440\sl276\slmult1\b0 JFS:\tab A user interface component framework for web applications that allows you to include UI components (such as fields and buttons) on a XHTML page, called a Facelets page; convert and validate UI component data; save UI component data to server-side data stores; and maintain component state.\b\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b0 Expression Language: A set of standard tags used in Facelets pages to refer to Java EE components\b\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b0 Servlets:\tab Java programming language classes that dynamically process requests and construct responses, usually for HTML pages.\b\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b0 Contexts and Dependency Injection for Java EE: A set of contextual services that make it easy for developers to use enterprise beans along with JavaServer Faces technology in web applications.\b\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The Business Tier \b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1080\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The business tier consists of components that provide the business logic for an application. The following Java EE technologies are among those that are used in the business tier:\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1440\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Enterprise JavaBeans (enterprise bean) components\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}AX-RS RESTful web services\par
